"The idempotency key must be a unique string up to 64 characters. We recommend using a UUID v4 to ensure uniqueness.",[169,542,544],{"id":543},"how-it-works","How it works",[546,547,548,552,564],"ol",{},[549,550,551],"li",{},"When you make a request with an idempotency key, our API stores the key along with the response.",[549,553,554,555],{},"If you retry the request with the same key:\n",[556,557,558,561],"ul",{},[549,559,560],{},"If the original request succeeded, we'll return the stored response",[549,562,563],{},"If the original request failed or is still processing, we'll process the request normally",[549,565,566],{},"After 24 hours, idempotency keys expire and are removed from our system.",[169,568,570],{"id":569},"best-practices","Best practices",[174,572,573],{},"Here are some tips for using idempotency effectively:",[546,575,576,583,589,595],{},[549,577,578,582],{},[579,580,581],"strong",{},"Generate unique keys",": Use UUIDs or another method to generate unique keys for each request.",[549,584,585,588],{},[579,586,587],{},"Store keys",": Keep track of idempotency keys alongside your request data.",[549,590,591,594],{},[579,592,593],{},"Set retry policies",": Configure your HTTP client to automatically retry failed requests with the same idempotency key.",[549,596,597,600],{},[579,598,599],{},"Handle errors",": Check error responses to determine if you should retry with the same key.",[169,602,604],{"id":603},"example-retry-implementation","Example retry implementation",[174,606,607],{},"Here's an example of how to implement automatic retries with idempotency:",[196,609,611],{"className":314,"code":610,"filename":316,"language":317,"meta":93,"style":93},"$vatly = new \\Vatly\\API\\VatlyApiClient();\n$vatly->setApiKey('live_your_api_key_here');\n\nfunction createCheckoutWithRetry($vatly, $data) {\n    $idempotencyKey = \\Ramsey\\Uuid\\Uuid::uuid4()->toString();\n    $maxRetries = 3;\n    $attempt = 0;\n\n    while ($attempt \u003C $maxRetries) {\n        t